reviews: Love their Gai Grob Pad Thai! It’s really good and prepared well! Their drunken noodles also have a spicy kick and very flavorful even though the portion could be bigger. Also had their spciy sea fried rice come with scallops, shrimps and squids. Their jungle beef fried rice was also excellent!

Best Thai in Boston!! Love it.
Had lunch today and loved it. Basil chicken rice, green curry chicken are authentic and delicious. The sticky mango rice touches a sweet spot.
Only 1 thing..they serve in disposable paper/Styrofoam.. that can be improved.

My daughter told me about this place a few times before visiting. She missed the fried rice so much that she shed tears as she took her first bite. I must say, though it looks bland the food is quite delicious, well seasoned and flavorful. I'll definitely be returning
One of my favorite Thai places. Best crab rangoons the pineapple sauce is so unique and tasty!

Tofu cubes - nice texture but not much flavor

Shrimps in a blanket - shrimps had good flavor. Fried outside was nice and crispy.

Tiny triangle - basically vegetable samosas. Good.

Wonton Soup- chicken wontons were rather dry. The soup itself was really good, though.

Pad see-u - Good. Bigger pieces of chicken were a bit dry.

Chicken sa-te - Good. Wish there was a bit more peanut sauce.
